Eagles Re-Acquire Running Back Jerome Harrison From Lions for Ronnie Brown

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-10-18T20:35:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/eagles-re-acquire-running-back-jerome-harrison-from-lions-for-ronnie-brown.html
The  Philadelphia Eagles  re-acquired
Jerome Harrison from the Detroit Lions for Ronnie Brown in a
swap of backup running backs at the National Football League
trade deadline.  Harrison, 28, spent eight games with the Eagles last season
and rushed for 239 yards and a touchdown. He joined the Lions as
a free agent and had 41 rushing yards in three games as a backup
this season. Harrison joins starting running back LeSean McCoy
and Dion Lewis in the Eaglesâ€™ backfield.  Brown, a 2008 Pro Bowl selection, joined the Eagles 2 1/2
months ago and had 38 yards on 13 carries in six games. The
second overall pick in the 2005  NFL draft , Brown rushed for
4,815 yards and scored 36 touchdowns in six seasons with the
 Miami Dolphins .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
